HEADWORD: deluxe
<hw>deluxe</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>impressively expensive;
notably exceeding typical price or quality.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gilded, luxurious, opulent, princely,
sumptuous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>especially elegant and sumptuous; of the highest
quality; <as>as, a <ex>deluxe</ex> car; <ex>deluxe</ex>
accommodations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gilded, luxurious, opulent, princely, sumptuous, de
luxe, luxe, luxury(prenominal).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

